////SEO (Search Engine Optimization) in YouTube/////////////////////////
YouTube video optimization 

Keyword Research:
- Before uploading, find what people are searching for.
- Use:
  YouTube search suggestions (auto-complete)
  Tools like TubeBuddy, VidIQ, Google Trends, chatgpt.com
Focus on:
  Long-tail keywords (e.g., “YouTube SEO for beginners 2026”)
  Low competition + high search volume

👉 Your main keyword should appear everywhere (title, description, tags).

Title:
- Contains 100 character (best 70-80)
- Start with main Keyword
- Use separator if needed (|)
- Add Modifier
- Make the title longer with more descriptive keywords
- letter counting you can use https://www.lettercount.com/ 
 
Description:
- First 2–3 lines are crucial (they show in search)
- Include your main keyword early
- Write at least 200–300 words
- Add related keywords naturally
-	Social Links
-	Subscribe my channel 
-	Use #Hastag
    Structure example:
      - Hook (with keyword)
      - Short summary
      - Links/socials
      - Timestamps

 
Tags:
-	Tags  = Keywords
-	Contains 500 characters  (best 450-480)
-	Must have most relevant keywords
-	Even you can use competitors key words
 
Thumbnails:
-	Size: 1280x720px
-	Image that can describe its contents
-	Text Based
-	High Quality Image
-	White & Red, Yellow & Black
-	Canva.com for Making image
 
Others:
-	File Name (Video and thumbnail ) should be same
-	Video Quality should be better
-	Video Ratio 16:9  (1920x1080px)
-	Channel age
-	Subscriber


 

